{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":642,"text":"Companies are losing control."},{"time":3802,"text":"What happens on Wall Street"},{"time":5407,"text":"no longer stays on Wall Street."},{"time":7738,"text":"What happens in Vegas ends up on YouTube. (Laughter)"},{"time":11624,"text":"Reputations are volatile. Loyalties are fickle."},{"time":15840,"text":"Management teams seem increasingly"},{"time":18416,"text":"disconnected from their staff. (Laughter)"},{"time":21440,"text":"A recent survey said that 27 percent of bosses believe"},{"time":24965,"text":"their employees are inspired by their firm."},{"time":27609,"text":"However, in the same survey, only four percent"},{"time":29756,"text":"of employees agreed."},{"time":32199,"text":"Companies are losing control"},{"time":34249,"text":"of their customers and their employees."},{"time":37891,"text":"But are they really?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":40141,"text":"I'm a marketer, and as a marketer, I know"},{"time":43438,"text":"that I've never really been in control."},{"time":46465,"text":"Your brand is what other people say about you"},{"time":49108,"text":"when you're not in the room, the saying goes."},{"time":52303,"text":"Hyperconnectivity and transparency allow companies"},{"time":56434,"text":"to be in that room now, 24/7."},{"time":59315,"text":"They can listen and join the conversation."},{"time":61790,"text":"In fact, they have more control over the loss of control"},{"time":64990,"text":"than ever before."},{"time":67380,"text":"They can design for it. But how?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":70430,"text":"First of all, they can give employees and customers more control."},{"time":73996,"text":"They can collaborate with them on the creation of ideas,"},{"time":77392,"text":"knowledge, content, designs and product."},{"time":80770,"text":"They can give them more control over pricing,"},{"time":83218,"text":"which is what the band Radiohead did"},{"time":85178,"text":"with its pay-as-you-like online release of its album"},{"time":88252,"text":"\"In Rainbows.\" Buyers could determine the price,"},{"time":91200,"text":"but the offer was exclusive, and only stood for a limited period of time."},{"time":96050,"text":"The album sold more copies than previous releases of the band."},{"time":100009,"text":"The Danish chocolate company Anthon Berg"},{"time":103206,"text":"opened a so-called \"generous store\" in Copenhagen."},{"time":106388,"text":"It asked customers to purchase chocolate"},{"time":108807,"text":"with the promise of good deeds towards loved ones."},{"time":112306,"text":"It turned transactions into interactions,"},{"time":115220,"text":"and generosity into a currency."},{"time":117773,"text":"Companies can even give control to hackers."},{"time":120734,"text":"When Microsoft Kinect came out,"},{"time":123185,"text":"the motion-controlled add-on to its Xbox gaming console,"},{"time":127336,"text":"it immediately drew the attention of hackers."},{"time":130272,"text":"Microsoft first fought off the hacks, but then shifted course"},{"time":134165,"text":"when it realized that actively supporting the community"},{"time":137028,"text":"came with benefits."},{"time":138787,"text":"The sense of co-ownership, the free publicity,"},{"time":142023,"text":"the added value, all helped drive sales."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145040,"text":"The ultimate empowerment of customers"},{"time":147369,"text":"is to ask them not to buy."},{"time":150462,"text":"Outdoor clothier Patagonia encouraged prospective buyers"},{"time":154389,"text":"to check out eBay for its used products"},{"time":157358,"text":"and to resole their shoes before purchasing new ones."},{"time":160925,"text":"In an even more radical stance against consumerism,"},{"time":164163,"text":"the company placed a \"Don't Buy This Jacket\""},{"time":166256,"text":"advertisement during the peak of shopping season."},{"time":169756,"text":"It may have jeopardized short-term sales,"},{"time":172558,"text":"but it builds lasting, long-term loyalty"},{"time":175212,"text":"based on shared values."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177382,"text":"Research has shown that giving employees more control"},{"time":180602,"text":"over their work makes them happier and more productive."},{"time":184371,"text":"The Brazilian company Semco Group famously"},{"time":187340,"text":"lets employees set their own work schedules"},{"time":190010,"text":"and even their salaries."},{"time":192022,"text":"Hulu and Netflix, among other companies,"},{"time":194293,"text":"have open vacation policies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196745,"text":"Companies can give people more control,"},{"time":199663,"text":"but they can also give them less control."},{"time":203935,"text":"Traditional business wisdom holds that trust"},{"time":206682,"text":"is earned by predictable behavior,"},{"time":209391,"text":"but when everything is consistent and standardized,"},{"time":212036,"text":"how do you create meaningful experiences?"},{"time":214959,"text":"Giving people less control might be a wonderful way"},{"time":218426,"text":"to counter the abundance of choice"},{"time":220688,"text":"and make them happier."},{"time":222370,"text":"Take the travel service Nextpedition."},{"time":225183,"text":"Nextpedition turns the trip into a game,"},{"time":228388,"text":"with surprising twists and turns along the way."},{"time":231960,"text":"It does not tell the traveler where she's going"},{"time":233784,"text":"until the very last minute, and information is provided"},{"time":236853,"text":"just in time. Similarly, Dutch airline KLM"},{"time":240836,"text":"launched a surprise campaign, seemingly randomly"},{"time":244021,"text":"handing out small gifts to travelers"},{"time":246813,"text":"en route to their destination."},{"time":248975,"text":"U.K.-based Interflora monitored Twitter"},{"time":251808,"text":"for users who were having a bad day,"},{"time":254318,"text":"and then sent them a free bouquet of flowers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258409,"text":"Is there anything companies can do to make"},{"time":260422,"text":"their employees feel less pressed for time? Yes."},{"time":263529,"text":"Force them to help others."},{"time":266454,"text":"A recent study suggests that having employees complete"},{"time":269788,"text":"occasional altruistic tasks throughout the day"},{"time":272599,"text":"increases their sense of overall productivity."},{"time":276668,"text":"At Frog, the company I work for, we hold internal"},{"time":280337,"text":"speed meet sessions that connect old and new employees,"},{"time":284938,"text":"helping them get to know each other fast."},{"time":287898,"text":"By applying a strict process, we give them less control,"},{"time":291220,"text":"less choice, but we enable more and richer social interactions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":295954,"text":"Companies are the makers of their fortunes,"},{"time":298810,"text":"and like all of us, they are utterly exposed to serendipity."},{"time":303073,"text":"That should make them more humble, more vulnerable"},{"time":306678,"text":"and more human."},{"time":309498,"text":"At the end of the day, as hyperconnectivity"},{"time":312344,"text":"and transparency expose companies' behavior"},{"time":314654,"text":"in broad daylight, staying true to their true selves"},{"time":318288,"text":"is the only sustainable value proposition."},{"time":321839,"text":"Or as the ballet dancer Alonzo King said,"},{"time":324484,"text":"\"What's interesting about you is you.\""},{"time":327494,"text":"For the true selves of companies to come through,"},{"time":330548,"text":"openness is paramount,"},{"time":333179,"text":"but radical openness is not a solution,"},{"time":336171,"text":"because when everything is open, nothing is open."},{"time":339581,"text":"\"A smile is a door that is half open and half closed,\""},{"time":344498,"text":"the author Jennifer Egan wrote."},{"time":346552,"text":"Companies can give their employees and customers"},{"time":349132,"text":"more control or less. They can worry about how much"},{"time":352619,"text":"openness is good for them, and what needs to stay closed."},{"time":356277,"text":"Or they can simply smile, and remain open"},{"time":360518,"text":"to all possibilities."},{"time":362135,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"},{"time":366246,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}